article.headline: East Carolina 86, Morgan State 67
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Darrell Jenkins led five players who had double-doubles with a game-high 22 points and 12 assists to lift East Carolina to a 86-67 win against Morgan State on Saturday. Jenkins also led the Pirates (1-0, Conference USA) with four 3-point shots. Freshman Gabe Blair scored 13 points and posted a team-high eight rebounds and Jeremy Ingram came off the bench to also score 13. Freshman John Fields had 12 points and three blocked shots while Cory Farmer tallied 11 points for East Carolina, which led 44-42 at the half. The Pirates shot 51.6 percent from the floor (32-of-62) and 42.9 percent from the behind the arc (9-of-21). Boubacar Coly recorded a double-double to lead Morgan State (0-1) with 20 points and 14 rebounds. Reggie Holmes added 17 points and Ronald Timus posted 12.
